'''Dr. Jeckyll & Mr. Hyde''' was a 1980s [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] group consisting of [[Andre Harrell|Andre "Dr. Jeckyll" Harrell]] and Alonzo "Mr. Hyde" Brown. The group was known for its corporate business image, wearing designer suits and ties while they [[rapping|rapped]]. The group first performed under the name "Harlem World Crew" and recorded on Tayster in 1980.<ref>[http://www.oldschoolhiphop.com/artists/emcees/jeckyllhyde.htm OldSchoolHipHop.Com - Dr Jeckyll & Mr Hyde Biography<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

Alonzo Brown joined [[Profile Records]] in 1981 under the name "Lonnie Love," and recorded the song "Young Ladies."

That same year, Brown teamed with [[Andre Harrell]] to make "Genius Rap," a well-received record which was one of the first hip hop records to used the famous [[Tom Tom Club]] [[Sampling (music)|sample]], "[[Genius of Love]]."

The pair ended their professional relationship in 1987, but Mr. Hyde continued recording with Profile Records, recording the solo 12", "The Witch" b/w "Hyde's Beat".<ref>[http://www.discogs.com/artist/Dr.+Jeckyll+%26+Mr.+Hyde Dr. Jeckyll & Mr. Hyde<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

After the group's demise, Andre Harrell became the founder and CEO of [[Uptown Records]]. He later went on to head [[Motown Records]].

Alonzo Brown went on to become a producer and screenwriter, serving as executive producer for the [[Judge Mathis]] show.

